<section xml:id="TI8" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Improper integrals (TI8)</title>
    <objectives>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <xi:include href="outcomes/08.ptx"/>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives>
    <p>
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Exploration1">
            <introduction>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Consider <m>f(x)=\frac{1}{x^2}.</m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </introduction>
            <task>
                <p>
                    Compute the following definite integrals.
                    <ol>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{0.1}^1 \frac{1}{x^2} dx.</m></li>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{0.01}^1 \frac{1}{x^2} dx.</m></li>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{0.001}^1 \frac{1}{x^2} dx.</m></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>
                    What do you notice as the lower bound approached 0?
                </p>
            </task>
        </activity>
        
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Exploration2">
            <introduction>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        We still are considering <m>f(x)=\frac{1}{x^2}.</m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </introduction>
            <task>
                <p>
                    Compute the following definite integrals.
                    <ol>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{1}^{10} \frac{1}{x^2} dx.</m></li>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{1}^{100} \frac{1}{x^2} dx.</m></li>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{1}^{1000} \frac{1}{x^2} dx.</m></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>
                    What do you notice as the upper bound approached <m>\infty</m>?
                </p>
            </task>
        </activity>
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Comparerootxtoxsquared">
            <introduction>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Now consider <m>g(x)=\frac{1}{\sqrt{x}}.</m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </introduction>
            <task>
                <p>
                    How do we think <m>\displaystyle \int_{a}^{1} \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} dx</m> behaves as <m>a</m> approaches 0?
                    <ol>
                        <li>The value of the integral will be bounded.</li>
                        <li>The value of the integral will be unbounded.</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>
                    How do we think <m>\displaystyle \int_{1}^{1} \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} dx</m> behaves as <m>a</m> approaches <m>\infty</m>?
                    <ol>
                        <li>The value of the integral will be bounded.</li>
                        <li>The value of the integral will be unbounded.</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </task>
        </activity>
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Exploration3">
            
            <task>
                <p>
                    Compute the following definite integrals.
                    <ol>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{0.1}^1 \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} dx.</m></li>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{0.01}^1 \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} dx.</m></li>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{0.001}^1 \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} dx.</m></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>
                    What do you notice as the lower bound approached 0?  How does this compare to what you found in <xref ref="activity-T8Exploration1"/>?
                </p>
            </task>
        </activity>
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Exploration4">
            
            <task>
                <p>
                    Compute the following definite integrals.
                    <ol>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{1}^{10} \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} dx.</m></li>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{1}^{100} \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} dx.</m></li>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle \int_{1}^{1000} \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} dx.</m></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>
                    What do you notice as the upper bound approached 0?  How does this compare to what you found in <xref ref="activity-T8Exploration2"/>?
                </p>
            </task>
        </activity>
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Compare">
            <p>
                How does what you found in <xref ref="activity-T8Exploration1"/>, <xref ref="activity-T8Exploration1"/>
            </p>
            
        </activity>
    </p>
</section>
